post_text:
Food for Families: The Plattsmouth Community Schools and OPAA! will be providing Grab-N-Go breakfasts and lunches at no charge for any child in a household from birth to age 18 regardless of income. Meals will be distributed by the loading dock in the staff parking lot at Plattsmouth High School, 1916 Old Hwy. 34. We will start on Wed., Mar. 25 with three breakfasts and three lunches per child. Then, we will move to Monday distribution of five breakfasts and five lunches per child on Mon., Mar. 30 and each Monday thereafter during our COVID-19 closure. It will be a drive-thru service each of the identified days from 6:30 AM to 9:00 AM, 11:00 AM to 1:00 PM, and 4:00 PM to 7:00 PM.

To help us get an accurate meal count, if you need food assistance, please complete the survey at this link (https://bit.ly/3a82V2r). If you are unable to complete the survey online, please call 402-296-3361 and provide the necessary information.

Please spread the word. Thank you.

#PLATTSMOUTHSTRONG!

post_text: Yes, our early childhood center was closed for two days, before it ever opened for 2019-2020, but the water main is fixed and our first day of school is happening on this fine Friday. Welcome back children and parents at our early childhood center!
text: Yes, our early childhood center was closed for two days, before it ever opened for 2019-2020, but the water main is fixed and our first day of school is happening on this fine Friday. Welcome back children and parents at our early childhood center!

post_text:
From Early Childhood/Head Start:

We have great news!

We are pleased to announce that our water main has been fixed and Friday, August 23 will be our first day of preschool at the Plattsmouth Early Childhood Center! We look forward to seeing everyone tomorrow morning!

post_text:
The bond issue passed at nearly 60%. Thank you to everyone that supported the bond issue. Now, Ameritas Investment Corporation is facilitating the sale of the actual bonds. This sale is part of the $15,055,000 that was approved for the bond issue. We plan to schedule another sale for the remaining portion of the bonds, in the future. Please direct all questions to Ameritas at 402-273-5405.

Stay tuned for an update regarding bond projects, near the end of July or early August. Thank you for your support.
